org.apache.ambari.server.orm.entities

Class AlertCurrentEntity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.orm.entities.AlertCurrentEntity

  • @Entity
public class AlertCurrentEntity
extends Object
    The AlertCurrentEntity class represents the most recently received an alert data for a given instance. This class always has an associated matching AlertHistoryEntity that defines the actual data of the alert.

    There will only ever be a single entity for each given AlertDefinitionEntity.

      • getOccurrences

        public Long getOccurrences()
        Gets the number of occurrences of this alert in its current state. States which are not AlertState.OK are aggregated such that transitioning between these states should not reset this value. For example, if an alert bounces between AlertState.WARNING and AlertState.CRITICAL, then it will not reset this value.
        Returns:
        the number of occurrences.
